<h1>Help</h1>

<p>The Recipe Box format is a simple, structured way to write recipes in plain text files that's easy to read and write.</p>

<h2>Example</h2>

<pre><code>= Chocolate Chip Cookies

# Cream together

  - 1/2 cup butter
  - 3/4 cup brown sugar

# Mix in

  - 1 egg
  - 1 tsp vanilla

# Add dry ingredients

  - 1 1/4 cups flour
  - 1/2 tsp baking soda
  - 1/2 tsp salt

# Fold in

  - 1 cup chocolate chips

# Drop spoonfuls on baking sheet and bake 10 minutes at 375Â°F
</code></pre>

<h2>Titles</h2>

<p>Recipe titles are prefixed with an equals sign:</p>

<pre><code>= Chocolate Chip Cookies
</code></pre>

<h2>Steps and Ingredients</h2>

<p>Steps are prefixed with hash symbols. Ingredients are listed under steps with exactly 2 spaces of indentation:</p>

<pre><code># Cream together

  - 1/2 cup butter
  - 3/4 cup brown sugar
</code></pre>

<h2>Multiple Components</h2>

<p>Recipes with multiple parts use a plus sign to create named sections:</p>

<pre><code>= Spaghetti with Meat Sauce

+ Sauce

# Brown the meat

  - 1 lb ground beef
  - 1 diced onion

# Add tomatoes and seasonings

  - 1 can crushed tomatoes
  - 2 tsp oregano
  - 1 tsp garlic powder

# Simmer 20 minutes

+ Pasta

# Boil water and cook

  - 1 lb spaghetti

# Drain and serve with sauce
</code></pre>